Newcastle teacher Khangelani Sibiya won the teacher of the year award. JOHANNESBURG - KwaZulu-Natal maths and science teacher Khangelani Sibiya recently took home the coveted Teacher of the Year Award from the Global Education Network. The award aims to recognise innovation and creativity in teaching. READ: Kenyan science teacher wins $1m global award Sibiya -- who uses dancing, sports, and sports to teach -- beat contenders from 79 countries. KZN MEC for Education Kwazi Mshengu congratulated Sibiya on the award. "He is the pride of our Province and the epitome of many exceptional men and women in the noble teaching profession," said Mshengu. 